t deserve it, then I received support from an officer, and I assumed I was in the right, until the other officers kicked in, then I realized I was in deep cocka. So now, I have realized my mistakes, and would like to make them up to the only family I have left, the only noes I hope I can trust. I wish, and pray that you will forgive me for my mistakes, and allow me back into the family I grew to love in such a short time. <p>"If you're going to kill, do it quick, to the back, where he can't see you," Maladwen Shadowlurker when he eluded the Dwarf Bounty Hunter.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uotomosoultearer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Otomo Soultearer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>High Council</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#939393>(4/8/01 12:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fbloodlordsfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A New Beginning</span><hr size=1> Hello Maladwen!<br>
